  "sentences": [
    {
      "id": "u9-s1",
      "text": "The history of food is never simple.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "history",
        "food",
        "simple"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s2",
      "text": "Think of ice cream.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "think",
        "ice cream"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s3",
      "text": "Many people see it as a Western dessert.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "people",
        "see",
        "Western",
        "dessert"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s4",
      "text": "However, this sweet treat actually came from China!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "however",
        "sweet treat",
        "actually",
        "came",
        "China"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s5",
      "text": "In the Zhou Dynasty, Chinese people began to store winter ice to enjoy in summer.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "Zhou Dynasty",
        "Chinese people",
        "began",
        "store",
        "winter ice",
        "enjoy",
        "summer"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s6",
      "text": "In the Song Dynasty, people started to make binglao - it just means \"ice cream\" in English.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "Song Dynasty",
        "people",
        "started",
        "make",
        "binglao",
        "means",
        "ice cream",
        "English"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s7",
      "text": "It was a lot like modern ice cream.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "lot",
        "like",
        "modern",
        "ice cream"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s8",
      "text": "Folk tales have it that Emperor Huizong suffered from stomach pains after eating too much ice.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "folk tales",
        "Emperor Huizong",
        "suffered",
        "stomach pains",
        "eating",
        "too much",
        "ice"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s9",
      "text": "In the Yuan Dynasty, Marco Polo tasted binglao and carried the idea all the way back to Europe.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "Yuan Dynasty",
        "Marco Polo",
        "tasted",
        "binglao",
        "carried",
        "idea",
        "all the way",
        "back",
        "Europe"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s10",
      "text": "People there added heavy cream and new tastes.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "people",
        "added",
        "heavy cream",
        "new tastes"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s11",
      "text": "The rest is history!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p1",
      "keywords": [
        "rest",
        "history"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s12",
      "text": "Sometimes, totally different cultures have similar dishes.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p2",
      "keywords": [
        "sometimes",
        "totally",
        "different",
        "cultures",
        "have",
        "similar",
        "dishes"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s13",
      "text": "Iranians love a kind of flat bread, sangak.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p2",
      "keywords": [
        "Iranians",
        "love",
        "kind",
        "flat bread",
        "sangak"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s14",
      "text": "People in Shaanxi, China, love stone pancakes.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p2",
      "keywords": [
        "people",
        "Shaanxi",
        "China",
        "love",
        "stone pancakes"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s15",
      "text": "These two look almost the same!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p2",
      "keywords": [
        "these",
        "two",
        "look",
        "almost",
        "same"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s16",
      "text": "People often compare roujiamo to hamburgers, a symbol of American food.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p2",
      "keywords": [
        "people",
        "often",
        "compare",
        "roujiamo",
        "hamburgers",
        "symbol",
        "American food"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s17",
      "text": "Many people call it the \"Chinese hamburger\".",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p2",
      "keywords": [
        "many people",
        "call",
        "Chinese hamburger"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s18",
      "text": "But in fact, arepas of Venezuela look more like the twin brother of roujiamo!",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p2",
      "keywords": [
        "but",
        "in fact",
        "arepas",
        "Venezuela",
        "look",
        "more like",
        "twin brother",
        "roujiamo"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s19",
      "text": "Food is a bridge between cultures.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p3",
      "keywords": [
        "food",
        "bridge",
        "between",
        "cultures"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "u9-s20",
      "text": "When food crosses borders, sweet things can happen.",
      "paragraphId": "u9-p3",
      "keywords": [
        "when",
        "food",
        "crosses",
        "borders",
        "sweet things",
        "can",
        "happen"
      ]
    }
  ],
